The paper discusses deep learning, transfer learning, and data augmentation techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on embedding inputs, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The paper also mentions improving model performance (cs.LG), and the use of pre-trained models (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the ability to identify classes of data not seen during training, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
